1
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:12,367
<i> I agreed to marry Edward</i>

2
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,100
<i>because I wanted my child
to be a legitimate Torrecampo.</i>

3
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:16,633
<i> You should be thanking me.</i>

4
00:00:16,767 --> 00:00:19,300
<i>You won't be separated
from our child.</i>

5
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:20,933
<i> They said I'm bad.</i>

6
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:28,267
<i>Paolo's mom said
I'm bad for Baby Jasmine.</i>

7
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,833
<i>What if you just agree
to what they want?</i>

8
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:34,167
<i>Just don't let Jobert
get close to Jasmine.</i>

9
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:36,067
<i>That way he'll still be here...</i>

10
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,233
<i>but there won't be
any more trouble, Marj.</i>

11
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:40,600
<i> I hope they agree.</i>

12
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:13,667
Sorry, Paolo,
for what I did.

13
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,900
My teacher said...

14
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,967
the dove means peace.

15
00:01:47,533 --> 00:01:49,200
Paolo...

16
00:01:50,267 --> 00:01:55,133
I don't want to hurt
Baby Jasmine.

17
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,600
No.

18
00:02:02,633 --> 00:02:03,900
I know.

19
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:17,967
Don't you want me anymore?

20
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,100
It's not like that.

21
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:26,667
I'm not mad at you, Jobert.

22
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,333
I just want to protect
Baby Jasmine.

23
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:38,633
And to keep her safe.

24
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:40,067
Always.

25
00:02:41,367 --> 00:02:43,033
<i> Do you understand?</i>

26
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:48,567
I want to protect Baby Jasmine.

27
00:02:52,467 --> 00:02:53,933
Then you'll do everything...

28
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:59,600
for Baby Jasmine, right?

29
00:03:00,633 --> 00:03:03,333
Yes, Paolo.

30
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:04,533
Marj, just tell me if you need
help watching Jasmine, okay?

31
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:06,367
Just tell me. Don't be shy.

32
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,833
Yes, Mom. I will.

33
00:04:08,633 --> 00:04:11,367
Mom! What's the problem?

34
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,067
It's nothing, Marj. Nothing.

35
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,533
- No.
- Marj, it's nothing.

36
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:17,767
Mom, what hurts? Lift your arm.

37
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:18,967
What is this?

38
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,767
It hurts, Marj!

39
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:24,233
Did dad do that to you?

40
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,300
Marj...

41
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:32,600
Your dad is cheating again.

42
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:35,500
I got mad at him last night,
and...

43
00:04:35,633 --> 00:04:37,433
this is what I got.

44
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:38,933
Mom!

45
00:04:39,067 --> 00:04:42,500
If you had just listened to me!

46
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:45,600
I thought he had changed, Marj.

47
00:04:45,733 --> 00:04:48,300
- Forgive me.
- Mom, listen to me.

48
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:52,833
Sorry isn't going to fix this.
Leave dad.

49
00:04:52,967 --> 00:04:56,900
Just leave him. Please listen.

50
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:59,400
Please, listen to me.

51
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:02,767
I know.

52
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,500
It's my fault.

53
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:08,800
I went back to Lito again.

54
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,600
I chose him again.

55
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:14,167
That's why our family
is falling apart, Marj.

56
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:17,100
- I deserve this.
- Mom, listen to me.

57
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:20,067
You don't deserve this.
You don't deserve this, okay?

58
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:24,667
No one who truly loves someone
would do this to them.

59
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,667
So leave. Pack your things.

60
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,900
Leave dad.

61
00:05:30,033 --> 00:05:32,500
He might do something
worse next time.

62
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:35,833
Are you listening?

63
00:05:41,167 --> 00:05:42,567
What else did dad do?

64
00:05:47,967 --> 00:05:50,233
I'm sorry, Marj. I'm so sorry.

65
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,833
Hello, Hannah?

66
00:06:08,967 --> 00:06:10,567
How's mom?

67
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:14,200
She's exhausted.
She's okay, though.

68
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:16,800
I'll take care of your mom here.
Don't worry.

69
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:18,833
<i> Thank you.</i>

70
00:06:18,967 --> 00:06:24,067
I'll send extra for rent
and whatever food she needs.

71
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:27,100
Sorry for all the trouble.

72
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:29,133
What are you talking about?
You are family.

73
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:32,067
Thank you again, Hannah.

74
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,833
Bye.

75
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:49,700
Marj,

76
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:55,367
can Baby Jasmine play with me?

77
00:06:56,433 --> 00:07:00,233
Maybe later, Jobert.
Jasmine needs to sleep.

78
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:04,200
Go play with Yolly
and Weng for now.

79
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:15,733
Are you mad at me?

80
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,700
I'm not mad.

81
00:07:22,933 --> 00:07:26,500
Paolo is mad at me.

82
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:29,367
And Paolo's mom.

83
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:33,700
And you.

84
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,567
Jobert, I'm not mad.
Stop crying now. That's enough.

85
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:40,600
It's because I'm bad.

86
00:07:40,733 --> 00:07:42,433
Bad. Bad.

87
00:07:42,567 --> 00:07:44,033
- Bad! Bad!
- Jobert, stop it.

88
00:07:44,167 --> 00:07:46,167
- Bad! Bad!
- Jobert, stop!

89
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:46,967
- Bad! Bad!
- Jobert!

90
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:50,567
You don't want me anymore!

91
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:54,500
Jobert, enough!
You're going too far! Stop!

92
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:56,100
Enough!

93
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,733
<i> Jobert!</i>

94
00:08:04,867 --> 00:08:06,333
Jobert!

95
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,100
Where's Jobert?

96
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,400
He's still locked in his room,
Ma'am.

97
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:34,400
He keeps calling
for your mother.

98
00:08:34,533 --> 00:08:36,133
He wants to see her.

99
00:08:37,167 --> 00:08:38,967
Then why don't you just take him
there?

100
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:41,167
If that's what he wants,
give it to him.

101
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:44,967
So we can finally have
some peace in this house.

102
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,700
I did suggest
maybe Jobert should stay

103
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,500
with Mommy Evelyn for now.

104
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,967
It's painful for Marj and me...

105
00:08:53,033 --> 00:09:00,233
but we'll all have more peace
of mind knowing Jasmine is safe.

106
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:05,500
I'm so sorry about this, Marj.

107
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:12,367
I know I promised
when you and Paolo got married

108
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:15,333
that you and Jobert
were a package deal.

109
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:22,967
But I have no choice but
to agree with Regina and Paolo.

110
00:09:24,667 --> 00:09:25,933
Dear...

111
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,400
Jobert needs to go.

112
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,867
Mom, I don't have anyone
on my side here.

113
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,133
I'm really struggling
with what they want.

114
00:09:51,267 --> 00:09:54,533
Marj, can't they be reasoned
with?

115
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:57,167
What if Jobert promises
to stay away from Jasmine?

116
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:59,033
<i> That's not fair.</i>

117
00:09:59,167 --> 00:10:00,367
It's as if Jobert is sick

118
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,567
that he's not even allowed
to be near my daughter.

119
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:04,767
That's not right, Mom.

120
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:09,000
<i> If they all don't want him...</i>

121
00:10:09,133 --> 00:10:11,733
maybe it's not good for Jobert
to stay here.

122
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:14,933
So what are you going to do,
Marj?

123
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,533
<i>Mom, I'm begging you and Hannah.</i>

124
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:22,200
Please take Jobert in.

125
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:25,800
You're the only ones he trusts,
aside from Paolo and me.

126
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,633
Please, Mom.

127
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:37,233
Don't cry, Jobert.

128
00:10:37,367 --> 00:10:38,633
I'm not abandoning you.

129
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,133
- I'll take care of you.
- No.

130
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:44,033
I don't want to leave.
I'll stay here with my sister.

131
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,967
Jobert, we have to do this.

132
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:51,767
You'll come back when Jasmine
is stronger and healthier.

133
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:54,467
When she's tougher,
you can play together.

134
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,933
You have to understand that.

135
00:11:01,067 --> 00:11:02,800
You understand, right?

136
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:10,800
I'll do it.

137
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:12,833
I'll leave...

138
00:11:12,967 --> 00:11:15,933
to protect Baby Jasmine.

139
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:20,033
Very good.

140
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:47,167
Yolly, why are you crying?

141
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,367
<i> Yolly...</i>

142
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:54,233
It's nothing.

143
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:56,900
I just got attached
to that child.

144
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:04,700
You haven't even known Jobert
that long,

145
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:08,800
but you miss him
so much already.

146
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,700
He reminds me of my son.

147
00:12:15,533 --> 00:12:18,367
If he were still alive,

148
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,600
he'd be the same age as Jobert
by now.

149
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:25,500
Oscar and I will miss him, too.

150
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:28,233
He's such a joy to be around.

151
00:12:32,533 --> 00:12:36,400
I just feel bad.

152
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:42,233
Our employers don't see
what we see in that boy.

153
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:46,000
He's so kind.

154
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:49,367
So hardworking. So loving.

155
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:52,833
Just because he's different

156
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:56,567
doesn't mean it's his fault
the baby almost got hurt.

157
00:12:56,700 --> 00:13:03,533
I'll listen to my sister
so she won't be mad anymore.

158
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:07,733
Jobert...

159
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:10,633
I'm not mad.

160
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,533
I will never be mad at you.

161
00:13:15,433 --> 00:13:17,533
I love you so much.

162
00:13:19,033 --> 00:13:22,100
We just have to do this
for Jasmine.

163
00:13:22,267 --> 00:13:24,033
Okay?

164
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:31,100
Marj...

165
00:13:31,867 --> 00:13:33,700
Give me a hug.

166
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:48,367
I love you, okay?

167
00:13:48,633 --> 00:13:50,333
I love you.

168
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:57,267
I love you, too, Marj.

169
00:14:13,633 --> 00:14:18,967
Yolly, we can't really
blame them either.

170
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:21,933
Yes, Jobert is very kind.

171
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:27,167
But we can't predict
when he might have an episode.

172
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:30,200
Like last night,
he was screaming, remember?

173
00:14:30,367 --> 00:14:33,700
- It was scary.
- What's scary about that!

174
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:36,600
He doesn't just have
episodes out of nowhere!

175
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:38,200
He was triggered!

176
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:40,867
And do you know why
he gets triggered?

177
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,700
Because of the nasty attitudes
of the people upstairs.

178
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:46,333
Yolly, they might hear you.

179
00:14:46,467 --> 00:14:50,033
If they hadn't questioned
that boy's worth,

180
00:14:50,167 --> 00:14:55,533
he wouldn't feel the need
to prove himself in this family.

181
00:14:56,867 --> 00:14:58,267
He wouldn't have tried so hard

182
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:01,367
that he accidentally
put Jasmine in danger.

183
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,133
Those people are the ones
at fault.

184
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,933
They're the ones to blame.

185
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:08,667
Yolly, let me get
you some water.

186
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:14,067
Here, drink.

187
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,500
That's enough.

188
00:15:32,567 --> 00:15:34,333
We're leaving.

189
00:15:35,467 --> 00:15:39,467
Thank you so much
for letting Jobert stay here,

190
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,967
even just for a while.

191
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,600
I believe
he can come back someday...

192
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:47,933
when Jasmine is older.

193
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:50,567
Maybe not.

194
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:57,300
I don't want my son
causing trouble for you again.

195
00:15:58,667 --> 00:16:01,333
And it's hard living with...

196
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:03,267
people who aren't normal.

197
00:16:11,267 --> 00:16:12,600
Marj.

198
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,067
- Mom.
- We're going now.

199
00:16:15,567 --> 00:16:16,933
Take care.

200
00:16:18,633 --> 00:16:19,833
Jobert.

201
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,667
Jobert.

202
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,767
Jobert.

203
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:27,267
I'll call you, okay?

204
00:16:29,133 --> 00:16:31,233
I promise, I'll call.

205
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:34,900
Look at me.

206
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:39,067
Don't forget that...

207
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:41,633
I love you.

208
00:16:45,300 --> 00:16:47,433
Jobert, let's go.

209
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:49,000
Let's go home, son. Let's go.

210
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:51,867
<i> Jobert...</i>

211
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,300
<i> Come on, we're going home.</i>

212
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:55,967
<i> Jobert, let's go home.</i>

213
00:16:57,033 --> 00:16:58,233
Bye, Marj.

214
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,533
Jobert.
Come on, what are you doing?

215
00:17:07,633 --> 00:17:08,933
<i> Jobert.</i>

216
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:13,033
Marj!

217
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:17,267
I want to stay here.

218
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:20,433
I'll stay here.

219
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:31,000
I'll stay here, Marj.

220
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:34,233
I'll stay here, Marj.

221
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,500
I'll stay here!

222
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:56,433
- Marj.
- Jobert, don't be stubborn.

223
00:17:56,567 --> 00:17:57,967
- Come on.
- Marj!

224
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:04,967
<i> Marj!</i>

225
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:07,167
Marj!

226
00:18:09,967 --> 00:18:12,667
Don't send me away.

227
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:16,833
Marj, please don't send me away.

228
00:18:18,567 --> 00:18:20,600
I'm such a terrible sister.

229
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:26,067
I'm such a terrible sister.

230
00:18:27,133 --> 00:18:29,600
No, Love. Okay?

231
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:32,200
You're being a good mother
to Jasmine.

232
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,033
That's the right thing to do.

233
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,433
<i> Don't worry, Jobert.</i>

234
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:05,800
<i>Just hang in there
a little longer.</i>

235
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:08,033
<i>Someday we'll live
in our dream house.</i>

236
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:11,167
<i> You, me, and mom.</i>

237
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:13,567
<i> And Pong.</i>

238
00:19:13,700 --> 00:19:16,833
<i>Of course, Pong comes, too.
He can't be left behind.</i>

239
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:22,800
<i>And I will give you everything
you want that's good for you.</i>

240
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:27,200
<i> Because I love you.</i>

241
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:31,367
<i> I love you, too.</i>

242
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,067
Baby...

243
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:40,967
look at this.

244
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:44,600
<i> Your Uncle Jobert made it.</i>

245
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:50,733
Jasmine, your Uncle Jobert
loves you so, so much.

246
00:19:52,100 --> 00:19:56,300
It's just a shame we can't
have him with us right now.

247
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:58,633
I didn't want him to leave.
But...

248
00:20:00,567 --> 00:20:01,800
I had to.

249
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,533
To protect you.

250
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:08,133
<i>Because I love you so much,
my child.</i>

251
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,633
So much.

252
00:20:49,267 --> 00:20:50,733
Jobert!

253
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:51,400
Hey!

254
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:53,333
Hannah missed you!

255
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:55,633
Jobert, hey!

256
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:58,367
I bought snacks for Pong.
Do you want to give them to him?

257
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:01,667
Is there anything
you want to eat?

258
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:03,467
Come on, let's buy something.
We'll order.

259
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:03,900
<i> Hannah...</i>

260
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,067
I'm sorry.

261
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:10,567
He just really doesn't want
to leave his sister.

262
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:15,600
Jobert, go upstairs to your room
for now.

263
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:18,033
You know the drill.
Same as before. Come on.

264
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:19,833
Yeah, let's put Pong here.

265
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:24,533
Let's set Pong down.

266
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,933
Enjoy.

267
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:44,333
How are you holding up?

268
00:21:46,067 --> 00:21:47,400
Here...

269
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,600
My heart is breaking
for my children.

270
00:21:54,567 --> 00:21:56,867
Maybe if I had been
a better mother...

271
00:21:58,533 --> 00:22:00,800
this wouldn't have happened.

272
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:05,433
Auntie, please don't pity
yourself like that.

273
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:08,900
Hannah...

274
00:22:09,033 --> 00:22:11,033
it's true.

275
00:22:11,167 --> 00:22:13,800
I put myself first,

276
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:15,733
and I neglected Jobert.

277
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:19,233
That's why Marj ended up having
to take him to the mansion.

278
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:26,167
But...

279
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,633
I've woken up now.

280
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:31,167
After all my foolishness
with Lito.

281
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:39,767
I'll do everything I can
to make it up to my children.

282
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,633
Marj has her own family now.

283
00:22:43,367 --> 00:22:46,833
It's not her responsibility
to take care of Jobert anymore.

284
00:22:49,933 --> 00:22:51,333
That's right, Auntie.

285
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:56,100
I just hope...

286
00:22:56,233 --> 00:22:57,967
it's not too late.

287
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,600
I hope...

288
00:23:02,933 --> 00:23:05,933
I can still fix my mistakes.

289
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:09,467
I hope...

290
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:13,267
I can still take good care
of my children.

291
00:23:15,167 --> 00:23:17,733
I hope...

292
00:23:17,867 --> 00:23:20,400
our family
can still be whole again.

293
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:24,267
It will happen, Auntie.

294
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:25,600
Now you're making me cry.

295
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:29,667
Okay, I'll take care
of Jobert's things.

296
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:31,567
<i> Please, have a seat first.</i>

297
00:23:35,067 --> 00:23:37,833
<i> Here, have some water.</i>

298
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:47,400
Your baby is looking healthy
at two months.

299
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,767
Doctor...

300
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:55,267
is that the baby's heartbeat?

301
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:57,733
Yes,
that's the baby's heartbeat.

302
00:24:07,067 --> 00:24:08,067
Doctor...

303
00:24:09,067 --> 00:24:10,767
where's my baby on the screen?

304
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,533
I can't really see anything.

305
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:18,200
Right now, the baby's only about
half the size of your thumb.

306
00:24:18,533 --> 00:24:22,167
Give it a few months,
and you'll see more clearly.

307
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,300
But, Doc, the heartbeat...

308
00:24:24,433 --> 00:24:26,967
it's supposed to be
that fast, right?

309
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,833
Yes, that's completely normal.

310
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:32,967
There's no problem, right, Doc?

311
00:24:33,100 --> 00:24:34,700
Hon...

312
00:24:34,833 --> 00:24:38,233
the doctor said
our baby's healthy.

313
00:24:38,633 --> 00:24:39,633
Don't worry.

314
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:48,167
I just want my baby to be
perfect when she comes out.

315
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:52,433
I have very big dreams for her.

316
00:24:53,967 --> 00:24:55,667
Don't worry.

317
00:24:56,033 --> 00:24:57,900
I won't let anything happen
to you.

318
00:24:58,033 --> 00:25:00,200
Our baby's going to be healthy.

319
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:12,467
<i>I'm just demanding
what I deserve.</i>

320
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,800
<i> You think you deserve Paolo...</i>

321
00:25:16,967 --> 00:25:18,500
<i>even though
you already have Edward?</i>

322
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:22,300
<i>I deserve for my child
to have a father.</i>

323
00:25:22,433 --> 00:25:24,133
<i>I'm pregnant,
and he's the father.</i>

324
00:25:24,267 --> 00:25:26,700
<i>You're going to make it look
like Edward is the father.</i>

325
00:25:27,033 --> 00:25:28,000
<i> That way,</i>

326
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:30,967
<i>the baby will still be
a legitimate Torrecampo.</i>

327
00:25:37,767 --> 00:25:38,900
You know,

328
00:25:39,033 --> 00:25:41,600
I think it would be better
if you moved into the mansion.

329
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:43,333
It'll be better for your child.

330
00:25:43,467 --> 00:25:45,567
I actually love that idea.

331
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,033
Do you think that's a good idea?

332
00:25:47,333 --> 00:25:48,500
Don't tell me
after all this time,

333
00:25:48,633 --> 00:25:49,800
you still have feelings for him?

334
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:51,900
She has bronchopulmonary
dysplasia.

335
00:25:52,033 --> 00:25:53,000
If she's not carefully
monitored,

336
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:54,833
the condition could persist.

337
00:25:54,967 --> 00:25:55,733
Jasmine?

338
00:25:55,867 --> 00:25:58,000
It's like she's not breathing.

339
00:25:58,133 --> 00:25:59,267
This is your fault!

340
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,600
If you had taken better care
of Jasmine,

341
00:26:00,733 --> 00:26:02,200
this wouldn't have happened!

342
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:04,133
I'll never forgive you!

343
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:07,200
Your niece is beautiful
and healthy, Paolo.

344
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:09,100
And don't you ever forget that.

345
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:11,100
She's Edward's daughter.
